WEBVTT

00:04.504 --> 00:08.717
[Instrumental music]

00:18.560 --> 00:20.562
Powertron!

00:20.729 --> 00:22.397
[All] Special attack!

00:22.772 --> 00:24.774
[Gunshots]

00:25.400 --> 00:27.027
[Grumbles]

00:27.527 --> 00:28.570
Curses!

00:28.737 --> 00:31.990
I'll get you next time,
powertron!

00:33.450 --> 00:34.784
Hold it, kingburg!

00:34.951 --> 00:37.037
Dammit! Did he get away?

00:37.162 --> 00:38.747
However, we powertrons
will uphold

00:38.913 --> 00:41.249
the peace of the network
without fail!

00:41.458 --> 00:42.458
[All] Yeah!

00:42.542 --> 00:44.294
[Upbeat music]

00:51.259 --> 00:53.678
[Boy] That was nothing
like the stuff on TV.

00:53.887 --> 00:55.847
[Indistinct chatter]

00:56.139 --> 00:57.891
- Let's check out a movie.
- Okay.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.226
Man, that's like way
too expensive.

01:00.393 --> 01:01.102
Mm-hmm.

01:01.269 --> 01:04.147
Like I said, it's from
that show in Hiroshima.

01:04.272 --> 01:05.940
You mean the one
I couldn't go to?

01:06.107 --> 01:08.068
Yeah, that time when rei
fumbled one of her songs

01:08.276 --> 01:10.320
and then those guys
started all that trouble.

01:10.487 --> 01:12.322
And this is the
minidisc from when

01:12.489 --> 01:14.491
mima had sung
in rei's place one time.

01:14.657 --> 01:16.701
Yeah, I hear
it's a real collector's item.

01:16.868 --> 01:19.412
Oh, yeah. So, like,
is that rumor really true?

01:19.579 --> 01:21.373
- What, the one about mirna?
- Uh-huh.

01:21.581 --> 01:24.084
- That's what everyone's saying.
- Fanzines, 400 yen.

01:24.709 --> 01:26.169
Cham! Fanzines.

01:26.378 --> 01:29.089
Three left. Only three left.

01:29.297 --> 01:30.757
400 yen.

01:31.091 --> 01:33.218
Yeah, I read about that too.

01:33.426 --> 01:35.762
And it's supposed to be
her last concert here.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.430
At a nothing show like this?

01:37.597 --> 01:40.183
I'd say that's
pretty cold of mimarin.

01:40.767 --> 01:43.561
Seems like there's been a lot
more solo acts going on lately.

01:43.728 --> 01:45.939
Yeah, but I think that
mimarin could really act.

01:46.147 --> 01:46.940
[Boys laughing]

01:47.107 --> 01:49.067
Hey, look, it's those guys.
Over there.

01:49.192 --> 01:50.419
- I thought it was great.
- [Man #1] Same guys who

01:50.443 --> 01:51.277
caused trouble last week.

01:51.444 --> 01:52.987
[Man #2]
Shit. Today of all days.

01:53.154 --> 01:54.948
They better not cause
any trouble.

01:56.866 --> 01:59.619
[Woman] Oh, I'm getting nervous!

02:00.203 --> 02:01.996
Rei, come on, please, sit still!

02:02.163 --> 02:04.833
Hey, what's up with this?
This is all frayed, ugh!

02:04.999 --> 02:05.792
- What are you doing?
- Where the hell

02:06.000 --> 02:07.502
is the masking tape?

02:07.669 --> 02:08.669
Hello? Yeah?

02:08.836 --> 02:11.131
Remember your entrance
in the second song, mima!

02:11.631 --> 02:13.091
Please, rumi, don't pressure me!

02:13.258 --> 02:14.258
I need a drink!

02:14.300 --> 02:15.778
- I'm sorry. I'll call you back.
- You can have drinks

02:15.802 --> 02:17.113
- after the show.
- Okay? It's just too crazy here.

02:17.137 --> 02:18.972
Alright, ladies, let's go.
Hurry! You're on!

02:19.139 --> 02:22.058
[Bell ringing]

02:22.267 --> 02:23.369
[Male announcer]
Alright, people.

02:23.393 --> 02:24.513
It looks like they're ready!

02:24.644 --> 02:26.479
[People cheering]

02:27.272 --> 02:28.898
So without further ado,

02:29.107 --> 02:32.026
please welcome to our stage...
Cham!

02:32.402 --> 02:35.613
[Pop music]

02:46.458 --> 02:49.169
[Train rumbling]

02:50.587 --> 02:54.007
[Music playing in headphones]

02:54.174 --> 02:56.217
[Indistinct chatter]

02:58.720 --> 03:00.513
[Rails squeaking]

03:04.017 --> 03:07.020
J“ at times you fear
for your love j”

03:07.353 --> 03:09.898
j“ send a little heart for her j“

03:10.023 --> 03:13.401
j“ and she'll be there with you,
with her love j“

03:13.776 --> 03:15.904
j“ waiting only for you j“

03:16.070 --> 03:19.574
j“ and when you love her,
love her, she will be j“

03:19.782 --> 03:22.827
j“ a little angel, angel
in your heart j“

03:22.994 --> 03:26.122
j“ you've got to push it,
push it for her love j“

03:26.331 --> 03:29.584
j“ and then forever, ever,
she will be j“

03:29.751 --> 03:32.212
j“ a sweet angel of your heart j“

03:32.420 --> 03:34.797
j“ to be there together j“

03:35.089 --> 03:38.092
j'j'j'j'

03:38.259 --> 03:40.220
[indistinct chatter]

03:46.976 --> 03:47.769
[Glass clinking]

03:47.977 --> 03:49.288
[Man] Could you get
a map to aisle five?

03:49.312 --> 03:50.396
- Yes, sir.
- Thanks.

03:50.522 --> 03:51.522
Uh...

03:54.317 --> 03:57.487
[Indistinct chatter]

04:00.156 --> 04:02.367
J'j'j'j'

04:05.119 --> 04:07.413
[cheering]

04:07.580 --> 04:10.291
[Cheering and whooping rowdily]

04:19.132 --> 04:21.427
[Tadokoro] Mima should
be acting, not singing!

04:22.470 --> 04:24.847
[Cries]

04:26.766 --> 04:28.309
I can't do this!

04:28.726 --> 04:29.769
Mika...

04:30.478 --> 04:32.522
They want her in a drama series.

04:32.772 --> 04:34.941
You just don't pass up
a deal like this!

04:35.108 --> 04:37.443
She can do both.
She can sing and act!

04:37.652 --> 04:39.332
Her schedule with
the other two has already

04:39.487 --> 04:40.738
created a difficult problem.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.050
[Rumi] Listen, she didn't go
to all those singing lessons

04:43.074 --> 04:45.076
just so she could
become an actress!

04:45.243 --> 04:46.828
The producer of the show
doesn't care.

04:47.036 --> 04:48.746
He thinks mima's
a wonderful actress.

04:48.871 --> 04:52.041
Of course.
But what about mima's feelings?

04:52.834 --> 04:54.377
- Huh?
- J“ waiting for you j“

04:54.544 --> 04:58.214
j“ and when you love her,
love her, she will be j“

04:58.381 --> 05:01.467
j“ a little angel, angel
in your heart j“

05:01.593 --> 05:04.679
j“ you've got to push it,
push it for her love j“

05:04.887 --> 05:07.932
j“ and then forever, ever,
she will be j“

05:08.141 --> 05:10.727
j“ a sweet angel of your heart j“

05:10.893 --> 05:13.187
j“ to be there together j“

05:18.651 --> 05:20.653
[Yelling]

05:21.654 --> 05:23.656
J'j'j'j'

05:23.906 --> 05:26.367
[cheering]

05:28.578 --> 05:30.538
Thank you very much.
You guys are wonderful!

05:30.747 --> 05:32.427
It was a fun concert,
but we only have time

05:32.540 --> 05:34.042
for one more song.

05:34.208 --> 05:36.502
We just got here!
You gotta sing more than one.

05:36.669 --> 05:38.338
[Cheering in agreement]

05:38.546 --> 05:41.633
Umm... but before we sing
our last song,

05:41.799 --> 05:43.119
we do have some news
we would like

05:43.259 --> 05:44.802
to share with all of you.

05:44.969 --> 05:45.969
You see?

05:46.012 --> 05:50.058
Uh, I, mima kirigoe,
had a really fun time

05:50.183 --> 05:51.577
- being a member of cham!
- [Man] Out of the way!

05:51.601 --> 05:52.601
[All gasp]

05:52.727 --> 05:53.728
I said out of my way!

05:53.936 --> 05:56.648
Get your slimy hands off me,
you oversized freak!

05:56.856 --> 05:59.067
- [Blows landing]
- [Grunts]

05:59.192 --> 06:01.611
[Indistinct shouting]

06:02.612 --> 06:03.696
Listen, you can't tell me

06:03.821 --> 06:05.406
what I can and can't do,
you asshole.

06:05.531 --> 06:06.908
[Man] Why don't you folks leave?

06:07.116 --> 06:08.451
What's that? What the hell?

06:08.618 --> 06:09.887
Who do you think you're
telling to leave,

06:09.911 --> 06:11.013
- you fucker?
- Hey, it wasn't me!

06:11.037 --> 06:12.037
I didn't say anything.

06:12.080 --> 06:13.956
- [Clattering]
- Ah, who threw that?

06:14.123 --> 06:16.459
Get the hell over here,
whoever threw that!

06:16.668 --> 06:17.752
Go home!

06:18.586 --> 06:21.923
- [Chanting] Go home, go home!
- [Grunts]

06:22.507 --> 06:24.258
Damn, it's those guys again.

06:24.467 --> 06:25.802
- We're canceling the show!
- Huh?

06:25.968 --> 06:27.053
But today is the...

06:28.680 --> 06:30.098
Shut up! Goddammit!

06:30.306 --> 06:32.016
[Indistinct shouting]

06:32.141 --> 06:35.561
[Chanting] Go home! Go home!
Go home! Go home!

06:35.728 --> 06:36.729
[Mirna] Stop it now!

06:36.896 --> 06:38.147
- [Grunts]
- Huh?

06:38.314 --> 06:40.024
[Microphone feedback]

06:40.316 --> 06:42.276
[Indistinct whispering]

06:43.569 --> 06:44.612
Tonight...

06:45.196 --> 06:46.948
I mean today,
I just wanted us to

06:47.156 --> 06:48.908
please have a good time.

06:50.368 --> 06:52.161
Fuckin' attitude she has
for a no-namer!

06:52.328 --> 06:53.621
Want a good time? Here!

06:55.456 --> 06:56.582
What the hell?

06:57.458 --> 06:59.460
[Breathes heavily]

07:00.837 --> 07:02.380
Damn weirdo! [Grunts]

07:02.880 --> 07:04.507
Let's go, you guys.

07:04.882 --> 07:06.926
[Indistinct chatter]

07:17.562 --> 07:20.064
[Stammers]

07:21.149 --> 07:24.569
A-Actually...
What I wanted to say is...

07:26.988 --> 07:29.198
This is mima's last
performance with cham!

07:29.407 --> 07:32.744
[All groan]

07:35.329 --> 07:37.248
Thank you all so much.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.777
I'm really happy that I spent
the last two and a half years

07:39.834 --> 07:42.712
being part of cham!
And sharing it all with you.

07:43.713 --> 07:44.839
I really hope

07:45.047 --> 07:48.050
that I can entertain you
just the same as an actress.

07:48.259 --> 07:50.386
So now, if you please...

07:52.096 --> 07:53.931
This will be my last song.

07:54.098 --> 07:55.558
[Indistinct chatter]

07:56.684 --> 07:58.394
[Somber piano music]

07:58.561 --> 08:00.521
[Camera shutters clicking]

08:06.652 --> 08:09.447
Well, it totally makes sense
from the agency's point of view.

08:09.614 --> 08:11.908
Pop idols just don't
make money, right?

08:12.033 --> 08:13.409
Metamorphosis, huh?

08:13.910 --> 08:16.913
J“ the day the sun was born j“

08:18.122 --> 08:21.292
j“ your warmth was on my laugh j“

08:22.502 --> 08:28.299
j“ remembering a day
when we loved each other j“

08:30.426 --> 08:33.929
j“ I thought that
was everything j“

08:35.097 --> 08:38.351
j“ your warmth was in my heart j“

08:39.393 --> 08:45.566
j“ remembering a time
when we loved one another j“

08:47.443 --> 08:51.697
j“ and now I know
that I feel like a coward j“

08:51.864 --> 08:55.368
j“ I don't feel pain,
just keep living j“

08:55.827 --> 09:00.081
j“ my face looks so pale
like a little white flower j“

09:00.289 --> 09:01.749
j“ do I still believe...? J“

09:01.958 --> 09:04.252
[indistinct chatter]

09:05.461 --> 09:07.588
[Laughs]

09:07.797 --> 09:09.757
[Camera shutters clicking]

09:12.677 --> 09:14.470
Mimarin! Mimarin!
Here, here, take this!

09:14.637 --> 09:15.680
Thank you.

09:16.264 --> 09:18.558
[Man] I'm always
watching mima's room!

09:20.142 --> 09:23.187
[Train passing]

09:33.739 --> 09:35.741
[Sighs]

09:40.830 --> 09:44.041
Yuck! This cheese
has gone bad already!

09:44.208 --> 09:45.293
[Clinking]

09:53.843 --> 09:55.887
[Bubbling]

09:58.723 --> 10:01.893
I'm sorry.
I forgot to feed you yesterday.

10:02.810 --> 10:05.229
- [Upbeat music playing quietly]
- [Sighs]

10:15.907 --> 10:17.950
[Man on TV] The earthquake
that happened in mie area

10:18.117 --> 10:20.620
flattened a number of towns
throughout the region.

10:20.786 --> 10:22.788
The government reports 200 dead,

10:22.997 --> 10:25.666
but the total number of victims
is yet to be determined

10:25.791 --> 10:29.003
while many more of them still
remain missing amid the rubble.

10:29.211 --> 10:30.630
Authorities have
called in troops

10:30.838 --> 10:32.381
for rescue operations, however,

10:32.548 --> 10:33.828
because the area
is getting dark,

10:33.966 --> 10:35.235
- [groans]
- And obtaining any source

10:35.259 --> 10:36.802
of light will be a problem.

10:36.969 --> 10:39.388
- The full operation...
- [Paper rustling]

10:39.597 --> 10:40.973
Well done, guys.

10:41.140 --> 10:43.351
Thanks for all the work
and good times.

10:44.018 --> 10:45.811
Bye bye, mima the pop idol.

10:45.978 --> 10:47.229
[Rustling]

10:47.396 --> 10:48.999
[Man on TV] ...Four ambulances
and emergency crews are

10:49.023 --> 10:50.650
making their way to the scene.

10:50.816 --> 10:52.044
- We have reports that the...
- [Grunts softly]

10:52.068 --> 10:53.545
Are being rerooted
through the surrounding

10:53.569 --> 10:55.237
residential streets,
and the police...

10:55.363 --> 10:57.573
"Sing for us forever."

10:58.157 --> 10:59.659
Guess I can't do that.

11:00.284 --> 11:01.803
A mother and her
six-year-old son today

11:01.827 --> 11:03.430
-tried to fit themselves into
-huh? Hmm...

11:03.454 --> 11:05.706
A shopping cart at a
local grocery store.

11:05.873 --> 11:07.673
As the mother was
unable to pry herself out...

11:07.792 --> 11:10.378
"I always like looking
into mima's room.

11:10.503 --> 11:11.503
"I'm linked with you.

11:11.587 --> 11:14.507
"I've put up a link
to mima's room."

11:14.632 --> 11:16.384
What the heck? Huh?

11:16.550 --> 11:18.427
It did end up taking two
paramedics to help

11:18.594 --> 11:19.804
the woman out of the cart.

11:20.012 --> 11:22.014
She was unhurt.
Apparently the cart...

11:22.306 --> 11:24.266
-[Telephone ringing] {Gasps}

11:30.439 --> 11:31.148
Hello?

11:31.357 --> 11:33.109
[Woman]
Mima, honey, you're home!

11:33.317 --> 11:34.902
Oh, it's you, mom!

11:36.112 --> 11:38.823
Yeah, I'm doin' fine.
How are you doin'?

11:40.074 --> 11:42.410
{gasps} You did, really?

11:43.244 --> 11:46.580
Yeah. Today was the last one.
No more singing.

11:46.747 --> 11:47.787
What? What are you sayin'?

11:47.957 --> 11:49.959
You always said
you wanted to be a singer.

11:50.167 --> 11:53.087
I told you, mom.
I'm gonna be an actress.

11:53.254 --> 11:55.631
Honey, we have all been
waiting for your new single,

11:55.798 --> 11:57.967
not to mention your uncle
over in yamaguchi

11:58.134 --> 12:01.262
said he'd buy twenty copies.
Do you realize that?

12:01.512 --> 12:02.952
[Sighs] You just don't
understand how

12:03.014 --> 12:04.390
this industry works, mom.

12:04.557 --> 12:07.476
Well, [do understand that
singing is what you do best.

12:07.601 --> 12:10.229
Morn, the pop idol image
is suffocating me!

12:10.438 --> 12:12.857
- Besides, today pop idols are...
- [Telephone ringing]

12:12.982 --> 12:15.151
Oh, wait. Another call.

12:17.278 --> 12:18.946
Kirigoe residence.

12:19.864 --> 12:20.573
Hello?

12:20.740 --> 12:22.700
[Heavy breathing]

12:22.908 --> 12:24.160
H-Hello?

12:25.369 --> 12:26.829
Mm, ah.

12:27.038 --> 12:28.039
[Beeping]

12:28.247 --> 12:31.751
Wrong number.
Uh-uh, they didn't say anything.

12:33.127 --> 12:34.503
Yeah, I know what you mean.

12:34.670 --> 12:37.673
- [Beeping]
- Oh, wait a minute. The bath!

12:37.840 --> 12:39.717
Call me back in five minutes.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.428
[Grunts softly]

12:42.636 --> 12:44.013
[Water running]

12:44.180 --> 12:45.806
- [Telephone ringing]
- Oh, mother!

12:45.973 --> 12:47.516
Can't you just wait one minute?

12:47.850 --> 12:49.894
[Beeping, printing]

12:50.061 --> 12:52.480
A fax? Who's it from?

12:53.898 --> 12:55.024
{gasps}

12:58.527 --> 13:03.324
traitor traitor traitor
traitor traitor traitor

13:03.491 --> 13:06.660
[ominous music]

13:08.287 --> 13:09.287
[Grunts]

13:17.421 --> 13:19.882
[Mirna]
"Excuse me, who are you?"

13:20.883 --> 13:23.052
- "Excuse me, who are you?"
- [Man] Open up.

13:23.219 --> 13:25.763
"Excuse me, who are you?"

13:26.514 --> 13:29.391
[Indistinct chatter]

13:31.519 --> 13:34.313
Must have been the first take.
They're both good.

13:35.523 --> 13:38.651
[Indistinct chatter]

13:38.818 --> 13:41.487
[Man] That's #5. Bring in #5

13:41.737 --> 13:43.364
[mirna] What do you think, rumi?

13:43.531 --> 13:45.324
Do you know what it means?

13:45.783 --> 13:48.244
[Yawns deeply]

13:50.746 --> 13:52.123
It's just a website.

13:52.289 --> 13:54.083
Somebody took it off
the Internet.

13:54.250 --> 13:56.919
Oh, that's really
popular lately.

13:57.128 --> 13:58.712
Huh, so what's it mean?

13:58.879 --> 14:01.257
Hmm... how can I describe it?

14:01.382 --> 14:04.426
It's kind of like networking
by using the computer.

14:04.593 --> 14:05.594
Yeah, and?

14:05.761 --> 14:08.097
Well, it looks like this person,
whoever it is,

14:08.264 --> 14:09.849
put up a link to "mima's room",

14:10.057 --> 14:12.184
which is the title
of the website.

14:13.227 --> 14:14.227
That make sense?

14:14.270 --> 14:15.771
[Giggles] Not one bit.

14:15.938 --> 14:16.730
[Man] Alright!

14:16.939 --> 14:18.607
Sorry to keep you waiting.

14:19.233 --> 14:21.026
We 're ready for the take!

14:24.530 --> 14:27.283
[Woman and man laugh]

14:27.449 --> 14:29.201
Don't make me laugh!

14:30.077 --> 14:31.453
But I like to hear you laugh.

14:32.580 --> 14:33.580
5 seconds!

14:33.873 --> 14:37.168
- 4, 3, 2...
- [Clears throat]

14:38.627 --> 14:40.796
The murder victim, rika,
her younger sister is here.

14:40.963 --> 14:42.381
Would you like to see her?

14:42.548 --> 14:44.216
Mr. Yamashiro.

14:45.342 --> 14:46.468
Yes?

14:46.677 --> 14:48.721
Tell me, do you have
any idea why the culprit

14:48.888 --> 14:50.806
peels off the skin
of his victims?

14:50.931 --> 14:53.184
Uh, I assume he gets

14:53.350 --> 14:56.228
sexual stimulation
from such activities.

14:56.937 --> 14:58.022
He wants to become one.

14:58.189 --> 14:59.732
Forgive me. Become what?

15:00.691 --> 15:03.903
A woman, or perhaps...

15:04.486 --> 15:05.946
[Director] Ah, cut!

15:06.197 --> 15:07.197
[Groans]

15:07.698 --> 15:10.743
Eri ochiai is a great
actress after all!

15:10.910 --> 15:13.037
She's a different person
so completely involved

15:13.204 --> 15:14.413
when the camera is rolling!

15:14.580 --> 15:15.623
[Director] That's good!

15:15.789 --> 15:18.167
[Man] Okay, scene 32!

15:18.751 --> 15:20.729
- [Man #2] Moving on, people.
- Hey, rika's sister!

15:20.753 --> 15:22.213
We're ready for ya!

15:22.379 --> 15:23.379
Here!

15:25.049 --> 15:26.050
- Hold this!
- Alright.

15:26.217 --> 15:27.927
- You nervous?
- A bit.

15:28.427 --> 15:29.511
Hmm.

15:33.557 --> 15:36.769
She only has one line.
What's she nervous about?

15:38.854 --> 15:41.106
Well, how's our
star actress so far?

15:41.357 --> 15:43.567
Mr. Tadokoro.
She's just going on now.

15:48.072 --> 15:49.698
"Excuse me, who are you?"

15:49.907 --> 15:51.116
"Excuse me, who are you?"

15:51.283 --> 15:52.677
- People, this is a hot set.
- "Excuse..."

15:52.701 --> 15:54.262
- Please do not touch anything.
- [Slow piano music]

15:54.286 --> 15:57.081
- [Laughter, indistinct chatter]
- Get down people.

15:57.248 --> 15:59.128
- You see, that's what I mean!
- You believe it?

15:59.291 --> 16:01.293
[All laugh]

16:04.088 --> 16:06.131
[Man] Man, I'm exhausted.

16:07.132 --> 16:08.759
Eri looks very pretty,
doesn't she?

16:09.969 --> 16:12.129
[Man] Bring that in quickly,
quickly, quickly, quickly!

16:15.891 --> 16:18.269
[Distorted laughter]

16:18.894 --> 16:19.894
Mm.

16:20.020 --> 16:20.813
[Man] Alright, everybody.

16:20.980 --> 16:22.832
[Man #2] Alright lets...
Let's get this going quickly.

16:22.856 --> 16:24.376
[Woman] Hey can I
get an apple box over here?

16:24.400 --> 16:26.044
- [Man] You got it.
- Ugh, cup of coffee...

16:26.068 --> 16:27.486
- Good morning.
- Good morning!

16:28.237 --> 16:30.781
Good morning.
Well, hello, everyone.

16:30.948 --> 16:32.157
[All] Good morning.

16:32.283 --> 16:33.909
Mr. Shibuya,
you decided to come.

16:34.118 --> 16:35.118
Hi, eri, how's it going?

16:35.244 --> 16:36.787
How's my script
holdin' out for ya?

16:37.037 --> 16:39.623
Mm, your words are so difficult,
Mr. Shibuya.

16:39.832 --> 16:41.417
I think I'll have to quit.

16:41.583 --> 16:43.168
Eri, please don't say that.

16:43.377 --> 16:46.046
Oh, it's the best.
I just love it!

16:46.171 --> 16:47.756
You've really outdone yourself.

16:47.923 --> 16:49.508
Oh, you little devil, you.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.927
Eri, darling,
I have these fan letters.

16:52.052 --> 16:53.989
They were sent to the station.
They're all for you.

16:54.013 --> 16:56.223
Oh, thank you, Mr. Tejima.

16:56.432 --> 16:57.433
Kuro?

16:59.143 --> 17:01.687
Oh, this one's not for you.

17:02.438 --> 17:05.232
Well, keep up the good work.
I'm back to mine.

17:05.482 --> 17:07.776
So, Mr. Shibuya,
you have to tell me.

17:07.943 --> 17:09.343
Who ends up being
the criminal, hmm?

17:09.486 --> 17:12.948
Sorry, can't tell you.
That'd spoil the fun.

17:14.616 --> 17:17.243
So what are you going to
do about the criminal?

17:17.536 --> 17:20.497
You're running out of time.
You gotta make a decision soon.

17:20.664 --> 17:21.874
Mm...

17:23.041 --> 17:25.127
Good morning, Mr. Tejima.
Mr. Shibuya.

17:25.252 --> 17:28.380
How's everything going, huh?
How's everything?

17:28.797 --> 17:30.049
Ah, hello there.

17:30.257 --> 17:32.509
Everyone tells me that
mima's doing great.

17:32.676 --> 17:34.053
Well, if that's the case,

17:34.219 --> 17:37.348
don't you feel that she's
not doing enough? [Laughs]

17:37.639 --> 17:39.266
- Did you hear that, shibuya?
- Huh?

17:39.516 --> 17:41.769
Hey, don't look at me!
It's not my decision.

17:41.977 --> 17:44.313
Help me out here.
Please, would ya?

17:44.480 --> 17:47.358
Try and make use of mima
just a little bit more!

17:47.900 --> 17:50.778
Ah... she's a pop idol,
understand?

17:50.986 --> 17:52.237
They're just so hard to use.

17:52.363 --> 17:53.822
No problem! It's easy,

17:53.989 --> 17:55.741
she's done with
being a pop idol!

17:55.908 --> 17:56.908
Really?

17:57.117 --> 18:00.120
[Tadokoro] We also want to give
her a drastic image change.

18:00.621 --> 18:02.122
[Man] We 're ready for the take!

18:04.666 --> 18:06.877
Almost forgot, this is for mima.

18:07.252 --> 18:08.962
Your hair is, like,
shining in the light.

18:09.129 --> 18:10.130
It's very pretty.

18:10.297 --> 18:11.840
"Excuse me, who are you?"

18:12.007 --> 18:13.217
"Excuse me, who are you?"

18:13.384 --> 18:14.676
5 seconds!

18:14.927 --> 18:18.347
- "Excuse me..."
- 4, 3, 2...

18:20.307 --> 18:21.433
- [Explosion]
- Ah!

18:21.600 --> 18:22.351
[All gasp]

18:22.518 --> 18:24.520
[Ominous music]

18:24.937 --> 18:26.230
Mr. Tadokoro?

18:27.147 --> 18:28.857
Oh, my god, what happened?

18:30.859 --> 18:32.903
- [Grunts]
- Mr. Tadokoro!

18:37.157 --> 18:38.367
I'm alright.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.577
What in the hell was that?

18:41.161 --> 18:43.330
I think that the
letter just exploded.

18:43.497 --> 18:45.457
Call an ambulance quick!

18:45.582 --> 18:46.667
[Man] Got it!

18:47.418 --> 18:51.338
Is a warning.
The next one will be real.

18:51.547 --> 18:54.508
- [Ominous music]
- [Indistinct chatter]

18:59.930 --> 19:02.766
[Siren wailing in distance]

19:09.857 --> 19:11.859
[Clicking]

19:15.529 --> 19:18.532
[Sighs] Okay, we're all set now.

19:18.699 --> 19:20.742
Rumi, you're so amazing!
Thank you!

19:20.909 --> 19:23.787
And now, I'll sign you up
for online services, okay?

19:23.954 --> 19:24.997
Okay.

19:25.289 --> 19:26.373
Oh...

19:26.957 --> 19:29.668
Rumi, I was just
wondering about...

19:29.877 --> 19:30.711
About what?

19:30.878 --> 19:32.439
- About the other day.
- [Keyboard clacking]

19:32.463 --> 19:35.048
Oh, that? Okay...

19:35.424 --> 19:37.551
Credit card number...

19:38.677 --> 19:40.029
Don't you think we
should have at least

19:40.053 --> 19:41.638
let the police know about it?

19:42.347 --> 19:44.057
Mr. Tadokoro said not to.

19:44.224 --> 19:46.643
He doesn't want us to
do anything about it.

19:47.686 --> 19:50.272
But it was... I mean,
a crime was committed.

19:50.439 --> 19:51.458
And if you think about it,

19:51.482 --> 19:53.567
I could have been the one
that opened that letter.

19:53.692 --> 19:56.236
Everything's okay now.
It was just a prank.

19:56.361 --> 19:58.739
Fortunately, Mr. Tadokoro
wasn't badly hurt,

19:58.947 --> 20:01.992
so you shouldn't worry about
it anymore, mima, alright?

20:02.826 --> 20:04.095
- Yeah...
- Now I have to explain

20:04.119 --> 20:06.038
this all to you,
so listen carefully.

20:06.246 --> 20:07.246
Okay!

20:07.706 --> 20:10.209
This is a browser for
the world wide web.

20:10.417 --> 20:12.753
You launch it by
double-clicking here.

20:13.587 --> 20:15.380
[Mirna] What? Double-clip?

20:15.964 --> 20:17.404
What are you going
to do with a clip?

20:17.508 --> 20:18.748
I thought that's what you said!

20:18.884 --> 20:21.887
No, see, at the location here,
you enter the url.

20:22.054 --> 20:24.223
It's really not that
difficult to understand.

20:24.389 --> 20:26.433
Oh, rumi, come on!

20:26.600 --> 20:29.561
Will you please explain
it to me in English?

20:29.770 --> 20:31.897
Oh, boy.
Whatever gave you the idea

20:32.064 --> 20:33.524
to buy a computer anyway?

20:33.690 --> 20:36.026
Because they said it was easy!

20:36.193 --> 20:39.029
Alright, I'll explain it from
the beginning once more.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.238
Okay!

20:48.580 --> 20:51.750
- [Mima] H... t... t... p...
- [Keyboard clacking]

20:56.880 --> 20:58.590
Ooh, something came up!

20:59.508 --> 21:01.927
Hey, I'm not so bad at this.

21:02.052 --> 21:03.637
Now, let's see. Hmm...

21:04.471 --> 21:06.473
{gasps} There it is!

21:06.640 --> 21:08.600
Mima's room

21:08.767 --> 21:09.768
oh!

21:11.687 --> 21:12.688
Mima's room

21:12.896 --> 21:13.647
mima's diary

21:13.772 --> 21:14.898
"it was just terrible!"

21:15.107 --> 21:17.568
"I screwed up the choreography,
and forgot my lyrics.

21:17.693 --> 21:20.362
"I feel so sorry
for all my fans!

21:20.612 --> 21:23.198
"This morning, when [got off
the train left foot first,

21:23.407 --> 21:24.992
"all the bad stuff started.

21:25.158 --> 21:26.803
"I always make it a point
that my right foot

21:26.827 --> 21:29.913
"goes first into the
train and into the bath."

21:30.080 --> 21:32.082
[Laughs]

21:32.249 --> 21:34.626
Someone sure knows me!
What's this?

21:35.002 --> 21:36.878
"Today was my 21st birthday.

21:37.087 --> 21:40.257
"Yukiko, rei, and the staff at
the agency held a party for me.

21:40.382 --> 21:41.466
"It was terrific!

21:41.592 --> 21:44.261
"Coming home, I went grocery
shopping at the usual store.

21:44.720 --> 21:46.930
"I bought myself
mineral water and milk.

21:47.097 --> 21:48.223
"I get the best water,

21:48.432 --> 21:50.642
"and the milk just
has to be cow brand.

21:51.310 --> 21:54.062
"I have to allow myself
at least that luxury.

21:54.229 --> 21:55.949
"And of course I get
the right brand of food

21:56.064 --> 21:59.318
for my precious fish,
the kind they like."

22:00.193 --> 22:01.778
"May 12th. I was impressed with

22:01.987 --> 22:04.197
"eri ochiai's performance
in double bind.

22:04.323 --> 22:08.452
"She's becomes another person
when the camera is rolling."

22:08.660 --> 22:10.078
Where did this come from?

22:10.287 --> 22:11.663
How do they know so much?

22:11.830 --> 22:13.999
- [Clicks]
- Excuse me, who are you?

22:14.207 --> 22:15.207
[Ominous music]

22:15.334 --> 22:16.668
Excuse me, who are you?

22:17.961 --> 22:19.796
Excuse me, who are you?

22:20.797 --> 22:22.758
Excuse me, who are you?

22:23.550 --> 22:25.719
Excuse me, who are you?

22:26.261 --> 22:28.096
Excuse me, who are you?

22:28.930 --> 22:30.390
[Indistinct chatter]

22:30.557 --> 22:32.809
Excuse me, who are you?

22:33.226 --> 22:36.271
Dr. Asamiya,
specializing in psychiatry.

22:36.480 --> 22:37.939
I was your
sister's psychiatrist.

22:38.106 --> 22:40.400
- I'm very sorry this happened.
- [Man pants]

22:40.817 --> 22:42.277
However, there are some things

22:42.527 --> 22:44.088
- I'd like to ask you.
- Detective yamashiro.

22:44.112 --> 22:45.572
- Another one.
- What?

22:45.739 --> 22:47.866
[Upbeat music]

22:51.453 --> 22:52.537
[Shutters clicking]

22:52.663 --> 22:54.581
[Woman screams]

23:06.051 --> 23:08.470
This looks like
the fifth victim.

23:11.598 --> 23:13.392
[Rumi] Just three shots of her?

23:14.518 --> 23:16.019
[Groans]

23:16.186 --> 23:17.604
Do you really think
this is worth it

23:17.771 --> 23:19.022
for her to leave cham!?

23:19.189 --> 23:20.189
Do you?

23:20.232 --> 23:21.483
Rumi, darling.

23:21.650 --> 23:23.402
Do you know how
much work it is in getting a

23:23.568 --> 23:25.654
- recurring role in a series?
- [Lighter clicking]

23:25.821 --> 23:27.823
I understand all that.

23:27.989 --> 23:29.282
However...

23:30.200 --> 23:31.326
[Exhales]

23:31.493 --> 23:33.161
This is when
mima proves herself.

23:33.328 --> 23:36.623
She's very close to establishing
credibility as a real actress.

23:36.790 --> 23:40.127
Right, but we should be
selling mima as a pop idol!

23:40.293 --> 23:41.670
Eh, come on.

23:41.837 --> 23:43.463
Times have changed
since rumi hidaka

23:43.630 --> 23:45.298
was a working pop idol.

23:45.507 --> 23:46.717
I know that.

23:46.842 --> 23:48.122
Nowadays,
there are no places for

23:48.301 --> 23:49.970
pop idols to appeal
to the masses.

23:50.137 --> 23:51.847
This is the turning point
that'll decide

23:52.013 --> 23:53.306
if mima lasts or not.

23:53.432 --> 23:55.809
Well, excuse me, sir,
for not surviving.

23:56.184 --> 23:57.477
Please, rumi!

23:57.644 --> 23:59.938
There'd be nothing better
than for her to be an actress

24:00.147 --> 24:01.356
and become a star.

24:01.690 --> 24:04.943
She came all the way to Tokyo
to make it as a singer.

24:05.110 --> 24:06.570
Rumi, stop and think about it.

24:06.737 --> 24:08.947
On record sales we
make practically nothing.

24:09.072 --> 24:11.491
It'd be fine
if she could sell more.

24:13.368 --> 24:14.786
Well, you know,
I do agree with you.

24:14.953 --> 24:16.747
I wish they'd start
using her a bit more.

24:16.913 --> 24:19.207
[Man] Sorry we're
not that profitable!

24:20.667 --> 24:22.002
[Both] Good morning!

24:22.753 --> 24:24.671
How's the new cham!
Coming along?

24:25.046 --> 24:26.089
[Chuckles]

24:32.637 --> 24:34.181
[Cars honking]

24:34.347 --> 24:36.057
Double bind

24:43.648 --> 24:45.400
[Pop music]

24:45.650 --> 24:46.878
[Man] It was totally worthless.

24:46.902 --> 24:47.986
Did you see it?

24:48.528 --> 24:52.157
Double bind. Yeah, I saw it.
It was boring!

24:52.908 --> 24:55.827
Do all psycho-thrillers made
in Japan turn out that way?

24:57.078 --> 24:58.997
Mimarin wasn't even in it!

24:59.289 --> 25:00.332
Yeah, she is.

25:00.707 --> 25:02.387
How many scenes was
she in last week? Four?

25:02.459 --> 25:04.211
- Nah, it was only three.
- Yeah.

25:04.377 --> 25:07.047
Will somebody save mimarin?
Please?

25:09.341 --> 25:15.180
A home page on the Internet:
You can make one too!

25:15.347 --> 25:18.350
- [Indistinct chatter]
- [Light piano music]

25:21.937 --> 25:23.522
[Woman]
Hurry up, the train's coming!

25:23.688 --> 25:25.899
[Man] I know,
I'm just getting a newspaper.

25:30.862 --> 25:32.840
This morning, when I got off
the train left foot first...

25:32.864 --> 25:34.157
[Man] Excuse me.

25:36.368 --> 25:37.744
[Grunts]

25:38.036 --> 25:39.996
[Pants]

25:49.589 --> 25:51.591
[Man] Come on,
keep it moving now.

25:52.843 --> 25:54.678
[Woman] Mom, I'm here!

25:58.640 --> 26:00.642
[Indistinct chatter]

26:15.782 --> 26:17.617
Hey, it's mimarin!

26:17.951 --> 26:19.303
- Good morning, mimarin!
- Good morning, mimarin!

26:19.327 --> 26:20.453
Hey, mimarin.

26:20.620 --> 26:22.747
- Break a leg with the series!
- Hey, wait, mimarin!

26:22.914 --> 26:24.708
Ah, do they get all unfriendly

26:24.916 --> 26:26.877
when they become
actresses or what?

26:27.627 --> 26:29.337
[Woman] Hurry up!

26:32.299 --> 26:33.717
[Elevator beeping]

26:38.096 --> 26:40.557
Hit-and-run at shinkaido.

26:40.682 --> 26:43.894
Tadashi do! (18),
in critical condition.

26:44.060 --> 26:46.438
- [Distorted music]
- Oh. [Gasps]

26:56.281 --> 26:57.949
Good morning, everyone!

26:58.158 --> 26:59.367
[Rumi] Good morning, mima.

26:59.534 --> 27:00.994
[Man] Cheers, everyone!

27:01.536 --> 27:03.163
- [All] Cheers!
- [Glasses clinking]

27:03.330 --> 27:04.956
[All laugh]

27:06.374 --> 27:08.251
- What's going on?
- Cham!'S new single...

27:08.418 --> 27:09.878
They're celebrating. Look!

27:10.879 --> 27:12.297
Wow! They got 83rd?

27:12.464 --> 27:14.382
I can't believe it,
that's great!

27:15.091 --> 27:17.427
We three never even
made the charts before.

27:17.594 --> 27:19.137
One, two, three!

27:19.262 --> 27:21.181
[Pepping]

27:22.223 --> 27:24.601
[All] Congratulations!

27:25.602 --> 27:26.353
[Woman] We did it!

27:26.519 --> 27:28.599
[Woman #2] Now we 're gonna
have to work really hard!

27:28.980 --> 27:30.357
But what about the audience?

27:30.523 --> 27:31.816
Will there be anyone there?

27:31.983 --> 27:34.653
Of course there will be, mima!

27:34.819 --> 27:35.819
{gasps}

27:36.488 --> 27:39.491
here's your next script.
It has a few more lines in it.

27:39.908 --> 27:40.908
0h.

27:41.493 --> 27:43.703
You've done great.
Both of you, really.

27:43.870 --> 27:46.247
Cham!'s doing great as a duo.
What can I say?

27:46.373 --> 27:48.500
[All laugh]

27:48.667 --> 27:52.087
- [Distant music]
- [Cars honking]

27:55.507 --> 27:57.509
[Indistinct chatter]

28:03.890 --> 28:06.643
Excuse me, are you currently
represented by an agent?

28:06.810 --> 28:08.353
I'm sorry, I'm in a hurry.

28:08.520 --> 28:09.520
0h.

28:10.146 --> 28:10.981
Come on, now.

28:11.147 --> 28:12.987
Wouldn't you be interested
in becoming a model?

28:13.024 --> 28:14.734
You sure do have the
look for it.

28:14.901 --> 28:16.319
A model?

28:17.570 --> 28:18.738
[Director] Cut!

28:20.281 --> 28:22.283
[Indistinct chatter]

28:25.537 --> 28:26.746
Okay, everybody.

28:26.871 --> 28:29.207
Let's move!
Set up for the next scene!

28:30.291 --> 28:31.960
[Man] Alright, next set up.

28:32.127 --> 28:33.837
Hey, who's that girl?

28:34.087 --> 28:35.630
I'm not sure.

28:38.216 --> 28:39.467
Oh, hey, shibuya.

28:39.718 --> 28:42.387
I saw next week's script.
You did a great job.

28:42.554 --> 28:44.472
It looks absolutely marvelous.

28:44.639 --> 28:46.307
I didn't expect any of that.
[Chuckles]

28:46.474 --> 28:47.267
[Laughs]

28:47.392 --> 28:50.020
Wait till you see.
It gets even better after that.

28:50.186 --> 28:50.937
I'm sure.

28:51.062 --> 28:52.981
But I'm beginning to wonder...

28:53.148 --> 28:55.900
If our darling mima can
handle that sort of thing,

28:56.067 --> 28:58.069
or better yet, her agency.

29:03.491 --> 29:05.326
[Pages rustling]

29:06.077 --> 29:08.329
[Tadokoro] Mima's character,
yoko takakura,

29:08.496 --> 29:10.582
completely changes
personalities when she's raped

29:10.749 --> 29:13.001
by the customers
at a local strip show.

29:13.168 --> 29:13.918
A rape scene?

29:14.127 --> 29:15.837
You have got to be
out of your mind!

29:16.004 --> 29:17.004
It's pivotal, rumi.

29:17.047 --> 29:18.840
She's the key figure
in the second half.

29:19.007 --> 29:19.758
Pivotal?

29:19.883 --> 29:22.010
-Mima is a pop idol! {Gasps}

29:22.260 --> 29:24.304
don't worry, mima.
It'll be alright.

29:24.471 --> 29:27.057
We'll ask the producers
and we'll get it changed.

29:27.557 --> 29:28.767
Wait, wait, wait a minute!

29:28.933 --> 29:30.769
The scripts are
behind schedule as it is,

29:30.977 --> 29:33.188
and the art crew is getting
antsy just sittin' around.

29:33.396 --> 29:35.940
I mean, how will it look if
we start complaining now?

29:36.107 --> 29:37.442
I just told shibuya that she was

29:37.609 --> 29:39.027
pulling out from
the pop idol scene.

29:39.194 --> 29:39.986
Will you stop already?

29:40.153 --> 29:42.572
It's our job to protect
the celebrities in our agency!

29:42.739 --> 29:45.742
There is absolutely no way
mima can do such a thing!

29:45.909 --> 29:47.077
[Mirna] It's alright, rumi.

29:47.827 --> 29:50.038
I'm an actress now.
I've made that decision,

29:50.246 --> 29:51.831
so now that's what
I'm going to do.

29:51.998 --> 29:54.793
- Mima!
- Ah, mima, fabulous.

29:54.959 --> 29:57.337
This kind of thing is
commonplace for actresses.

29:57.462 --> 29:59.881
Jodie whatshername,
she had to do it, right?

30:00.048 --> 30:02.092
Mima, dear,
please think it over.

30:02.258 --> 30:04.302
Do you realize what will happen?

30:04.511 --> 30:07.138
It's not as if they're really
going to rape me or anything.

30:07.347 --> 30:09.390
Although, I'm sure
my parents will flip

30:09.599 --> 30:10.850
when they see me like that.

30:11.017 --> 30:13.019
[Laughs nervously]

30:13.228 --> 30:16.314
Anyway, rumi, I'll do it.
I have to give it my best shot.

30:18.024 --> 30:19.317
Mima.

30:21.319 --> 30:23.321
[Indistinct chatter]

30:34.457 --> 30:36.209
I absolutely refuse to do it!

30:36.417 --> 30:38.253
-[Crashing] {Gasps}

